    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `(ii) That although the auditors had given a qualified opinion regarding '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the loss in the transaction of assignment of receivables and payables to IA, '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `there was no such qualification made by them with respect to transaction of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `sale of similar assets and liabilities with respect to another sister concern, '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ESJ, in which case there was no decrease in the fair market value of even a '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `single rupee. Whereas on the receivables transferred to IA, loss was recorded. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Both the cases were of companies falling under the same holding company. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Thus, there was no justification for transfer to sister concern IA of assets and '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `liabilities for a meagre consideration representing about 2 per cent. of the net '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 58>
   <String `asset value thereof. Further, in the resolution passed by the assessee, there was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `no reference of any loss incurred in the transfer of the asset, or valuation of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `inter-corporate deposits at fair market value, or to whom these assets were to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `be sold, or which assets were to be sold to which entity, or whether the draft '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `agreement had been perused by the Board before entering into the transaction. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Further, the agreement with IA for transfer of receivables by the assessee was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `an unsigned document. Therefore, the production of the board resolution did '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `not help the assessee’s case. The assessee also stated that the director’s report, '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `referred in the annual report, was not accessible to it and, therefore, could not '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FDW  -1.0%>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `be produced. The non-production of such a document went against the assessee'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `in proving the genuineness of transaction, the onus of which lay on the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `assessee. There was no reason to deviate from the orders of the lower author'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ities. '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `Section'>
    <FSize  10.5 pt>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
