   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `(iv) That as regards the assessee’s claim to treat the loss as a trading '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `loss, a study of the assessee’s balance'>
   <String `-'>
   <String `sheet showed the payables and receiva'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `bles treated as loans and advances and the amount of loss incurred was shown '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `as an exceptional item and in the cash flow statement, it was shown to be from '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `investing, not operating, activities. Therefore, it was apparent that it was not '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the assessee’s business to make investment in inter-corporate deposits. As a '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `result, the loss was not allowable as a business loss. There was also no force '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `in the assessee’s contention that it had offered the interest income as business '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `income and, therefore, the investment should be considered as a business '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `activity for the simple reason that the investment was held by the assessee to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `be an investment activity. While the assessee’s main object was shipping and '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `transportation, its incidental or ancillary activity of lending was not a busi'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ness activity to support its main object. Thus, the assessee’s loss was not on '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `revenue, but on capital, account, not constituting a business loss to qualify '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `for deduction. There was no infirmity in the Assessing Officer’s order to deny '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `deduction of the loss holding the transaction to be sham and intended to book '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 60>
   <String `fictitious loss, rendering it non-deductible as either bad debt or business loss. '>
