    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `9.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` '>
   <String `The '>
   <String `l'>
   <String `earned authorised representative submitted that submissions '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `were made before the learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals) on '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `February 18, 2021 which is placed at page No. 307—onwards wherein at '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `page No. 316 the assessee has cited the decision of the honourable '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Supreme Court in the case of '>
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77268134>
    <ETag `Reference'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77268140>
    <ETag `CRTo'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Italics'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77268147>
    <ETag `Title'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `S. A. Builders Ltd. '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `v.'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `Italics'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` CIT'>
   <String ` '>
   <String `(A'>
   <String `ppeals'>
   <String `)'>
   <ElementEnd `Title'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `CRTo'>
   <ElementEnd `Reference'>
   <FNote 1619>
   <String ` and '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `further at page No. 317 '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has submitted that '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee needs '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `time before the learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals) of 10-15 '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `days further to supplement the above submission in view of the statutory '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 72>
   <String `time line to file the return of income for the assessment year 2020-21 was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `approaching on February 15, 2021 and further the appellant has filed '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `several VSV applications for earlier years which were required for to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `frequently visit tax office to clear pending rectification orders and order '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `giving effects. Under these circumstances considering that due to '>
   <String `c'>
   <String `ovid-19 '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `related restrictions, the assessee wanted further time. Therefore, it was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `submitted that '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee could not submit the detail. As this was the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `sufficient cause for not adducing these details before the learned lower '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `authorities, now it should be admitted.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 78683467>
  <PgfTag `s10'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77303674>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Bold'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77358918>
    <ETag `Bold'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `10.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` The learned Departmental representative vehemently objected to the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `same and submitted that the learned Commissioner of Income-tax '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `(Appeals) has disposed of the appeal of the assessee on February 25, 2022. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `The assessee is relying on his letter dated February 18, 2021 wherein '>
   <String `the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessee is seeking time. He submits that the assessee has made a further '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `submission on November 8, 2021 before the learned Commissioner of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Income-tax (Appeals), wherein once again the assessee has sought time of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `10 days. He further submitted that since November 8, 2021 to February 25, '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `2022, '>
   <String `four'>
   <String ` months’ '>
   <String `t'>
   <String `ime was available with the assessee, but nothing was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `submitted before the learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals). '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Therefore, the claim of the assessee is that no time was granted to the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessee by the learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals) for '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `submission of the additional evidence is devoid of any merit and is an '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `incorrect statement. He submits that these is no reason given for non-'>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `submission before '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `learned Assessing Officer. Hence, he submitted that '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `additional evidence should not be admitted as no sufficient cause is shown '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `by '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 78683489>
  <PgfTag `s10'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77304186>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Bold'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77358967>
    <ETag `Bold'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `11.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <String ` '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `We have carefully considered the rival contention and find that these '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `documents are relevant for the assessee to demonstrate its case before the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Tribunal for effective disposal of the grounds raised. It is undoubtedly clear '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `that on February 18, 2021 '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has sought time before the learned '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals) for furnishing further information. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Further another letter dated November 8, 2021 was once again submitted '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `before the learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals), in the last line '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `itself the assessee has also sought 10 days’ time to supplement the above '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `submission. '>
   <String `The '>
   <String `a'>
   <String `ppellate order was passed on February 25, 2022. Thus, it '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `is evident that '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has been given enough opportunities to submit '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the details. There is no reason stated that why these documents were not '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `submitted before the learned Assessing Officer. However, we find that the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `additional evidence starting from serial Nos. 1-13 are with respect to the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `return of income and computation for the earlier years. The only additional '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 74>
   <String `evidence that has been submitted by the assessee is with respect to the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `board '>
   <String `n'>
   <String `ote relating to investment in subsidiary company, audited financial '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `statement of the subsidiary company and board resolution of assignment '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `of receivable and payable. We find that the '>
   <String `b'>
   <String `oard note relating to invest'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ment in subsidiary and its annual accounts are the main reason for which '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the disallowance has been made on account of interest expenditure on '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `investment made in subsidiary. Therefore, to decide that issue, these '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `documents are as such required by the authorities. In view of this, we '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `admit the additional evidence furnished.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
