   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `CIT '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `v.'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `Italics'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` Investa Industrial Corporation Ltd.'>
   <ElementEnd `Title'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `CRTo'>
   <ElementEnd `Reference'>
   <FNote 1620>
   <String ` the financial position of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the company being managed by the assessee deteriorated and the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `company went under liquidation, the assessee wrote of the principal '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `and interest outstanding from the company in its books of account '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `and claimed the same as a bad debt or business loss. Wherein the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `honourable High Court held if as a result of the managed company '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `having gone into liquidation, the advances became irrecoverable, the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `loss would have to be regarded as a trading loss and the same would '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `have to be allowed as a deduction while computing the income of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 87>
   <String `assessee. However, in case of appellant the fact is different, it has not '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `gone into liquidation and that the advances became irrecoverable.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para2'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 78683779>
  <PgfTag `Quotation1'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77325370>
    <ETag `Para2'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `5.10 The next claim made by the appellant that as per the provi'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `sions of section 36(2) of the Act, the amount of bad debt which is '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `written off as irrecoverable in the accounts of the assessee shall be '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `allowed as a deduction in computing business income. The basic '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `requirement to allow bad debt is that the amount claimed as bad debt '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `should have offered in earlier year as revenue. However, the year in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `which the revenue pertaining to its data was not offered with '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `evidence and the appellant has failed to justify the claim of bad debts '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `under section 36(1)(vi) of the Act. In absence of any critical evidence '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `before me, I am unable to accept the contention of the appellant and '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `held that the loss is a notional one and not actual loss.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para2'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 78683783>
  <PgfTag `Quotation1'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77325728>
    <ETag `Para2'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `5.11 Besides, claim is made by the appellant that it has been '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `consistently treating the interest income arising from ICD is and the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `receivables given to its various group companies as profits and gains '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `arising from business or profession in its return of income. This fact '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `has not been denied by Assessing Officer anywhere in his order. The '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `argument made by the appellant cannot absolve it from its liability. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `The Assessing Officer had placed on record the entire gamut of find'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ing and there is no further requirement for elaboration. In view of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `overall facts discussed as above addition made of Rs. 2,51'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `30'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `00,000 '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `on account of loss on transfer of ICD is apparent. This ground of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `appeal is dismissed.”'>
   <ElementEnd `Para2'>
   <ElementEnd `Quote'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
