   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77362975>
    <ETag `Bold'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `57.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <String ` '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `Regarding the claim of the assessee that '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee should be '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `allowed the deduction as bad debts written off under section 36(1)(vii) of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the '>
   <String `A'>
   <String `ct, we do not find that there is a write'>
   <String ` '>
   <String `off of any irrecoverable amount '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `in this case. The assessee has incurred loss on sale/transfer of certain '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `payables and receivables. Therefore, the loss cannot be claimed as bad '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `debt. All the arguments of the assessee that '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has fulfilled the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `provisions of section 36(2) of the Act as it has taken into account while '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `computing the profit for earlier years by including the interest income as '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `income are not relevant. Therefore, the learned lower authorities have '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `correctly held that the assessee is not entitled to claim the deduction of bad '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `debt written off in the books of account under section 36(1)(vii) of the '>
   <String `A'>
   <String `ct '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `as there is no write off of bad debt.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 78684349>
  <PgfTag `s10'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77343566>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Bold'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77363046>
    <ETag `Bold'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `58.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <String ` '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `Coming to the alternative claim of the assessee of the above sum as '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `trading loss, the learned Assessing Officer has categorically held in para'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `graph No. 4.6 of the assessment order that such loss was not incidental to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the business and nor was on account of revenue it was a future anticipated '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `loss and therefore it was disallowed under section 28(i) of the '>
   <String `A'>
   <String `ct. The '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals) has confirmed the finding '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `of the learned Assessing Officer'>
   <String `,'>
   <String ` we find that the assessee has sold its '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `payable and receivable. On careful reading of the balance-sheet of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessee-company, these are shown as loans and advances. Further the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `amount of loss incurred is also shown as an exceptional item and further in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the cash flow statement it is shown from the cash flow from investing '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `activities and not from operating activities. Therefore, it is apparent that it '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `is not the business of the assessee to make investment in inter corporate '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `deposits. Therefore, the loss of Rs. 177.50 crores are not allowable as a '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `business loss.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 78684362>
  <PgfTag `s10'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77343741>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
