   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `59.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <String ` '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `The argument of the assessee is that it has offered the interest '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `income as business income and therefore this investment should also be '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `considered as business activity of the assessee. We do not find any force in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FDW  1.0%>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `this argument for the simple reason that the investments held by the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessee'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` as investment activities. Further the memorandum of association '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 113>
   <String `of the company furnished before us as additional evidence shows that the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `main object of the assessee-company is of shipping and transportation. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `The serial No. 14 under the head object incidental or ancillary to the attain'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ment of the main object where lending is mentioned does not help the case '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `of the assessee because it is not the business activity of the assessee. It only '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `supports the main object of the assessee. Thus, the loss incurred by the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessee is on capital account and not on revenue account and it is not a '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `business loss which can be granted as deduction to the assessee.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
