   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `62.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <String ` '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `Ground No. 2 of the appeal is with respect to the disallowance of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `interest expenses claimed of Rs. 1,58'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `12'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `00,000. The fact shows that during '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the year under consideration the assessee has incurred interest expenses to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the tune of Rs. 1'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `009.57 crores and has received Rs. 142 crores as interest '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `income. The assessee has received inter corporate deposit and security '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `deposits from related parties on which interest expenses have been '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `incurred of Rs. 395.04 crores which has been debited as interest cost to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `related entities of Rs. 253.50 crores are on account of interest payment of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `intra corporate deposits taken from Essar '>
   <String `O'>
   <String `il Ltd. and Rs. 141.50 crores on '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `account of security deposit given by Essar Oil Ltd. The learned Assessing '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Officer noted that the interest income and expenses on inter corporate '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `deposit is considered then the assessee has paid interest on inter corporate '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `deposit of Rs. 253.50 crores and received an interest of Rs. 95.38 crores. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `These inter corporate deposits are taken from group entities and advances '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `are also given to the group entities. The assessee was questioned by the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned Assessing Officer which was replied by the assessee on December '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `17, 2019 stating that the inter corporate deposits have been advanced '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `during the business however no interest has been charged on certain inter '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `corporate deposits during the year. The assessee relied on the decision of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the honourable Supreme Court in case of '>
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77363435>
    <ETag `Reference'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77363441>
    <ETag `CRTo'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Italics'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77363448>
    <ETag `Title'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `H'>
   <String `ero '>
   <String `C'>
   <String `ycle'>
   <ElementEnd `Title'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `CRTo'>
   <ElementEnd `Reference'>
   <String ` stating that there is a '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `commercial expediency for advancing the inter corporate deposits. The '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned Assessing Officer noted that these inter corporate deposits are '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `from and to the group entry entities and no business expediency has been '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `established by the assessee that warrants allowability of claim of excess '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `interest expenditure on such inter corporate deposits more so as a business '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 115>
   <String `expenditure. He relied upon the decision of the honourable Madras High '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Court '>
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77363757>
    <ETag `Reference'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77363767>
    <ETag `CRTo'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Italics'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77363771>
    <ETag `Title'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `Mir Mohd. Ali '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `v.'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `Italics'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` CIT'>
   <ElementEnd `Title'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `CRTo'>
   <ElementEnd `Reference'>
   <FNote 1624>
   <String `, wherein it is held that it is for the assessee to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `prove that each of the loans on which he paid the interest was utilised for '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the purposes of his business. This decision has been affirmed by the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `honourable High Court in 52 ITR 165. Therefore, the interest income on '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `inter corporate deposit was considered by the Assessing Officer under the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `head '>
   <String `“'>
   <String `I'>
   <String `ncome from other sources'>
   <String `”'>
   <String ` instead of business income for statistical '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `purposes and further the excess claim of interest amounting to Rs. 158.12 '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `crores (being Rs. 253.30 crores minus Rs. 95.38 crores) were disallowed. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Accordingly, the disallowance of Rs. 1'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `58'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `12'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `00,000 was made by the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned Assessing Officer.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 78684422>
  <PgfTag `s10'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77344008>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Bold'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77363956>
    <ETag `Bold'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `63.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` The assessee challenged the same before the learned Commissioner '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `of Income-tax (Appeals), wherein the learned Commissioner of Income-tax '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `(Appeals) has confirmed the addition for the reason that when the assessee '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `has raised the business loans for the business purposes on which interest '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `liability is incurred for payment and on the other hand the funds were '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `advanced to sister concern for non-business purposes on interest'>
   <String `-'>
   <String `free or '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `on average interest basis, then the interest payable by the assessee to the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `financial institutions cannot be held to be used funds for business purposes '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `and no deduction accordingly can be permitted under section 36(1)(iii) of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the Act. The learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals) has also held '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `that the assessee has casually claimed that the said funds are used for the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `business purpose but has not established by the appellant during the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessment proceedings or before the appellate proceedings. He further '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `held that the contention of the assessee that the interest during the year is '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `lower due to the waiver of interest from two financially stressed entities is '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `contradicting the fact that inter corporate deposits were granted with a '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `view to earn interest income and margin in the entire process. Before the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals), no details were submitted '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `to counter the clear-cut findings of the learned Assessing Officer that there '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `was absence of necessary evidence to show that the amount borrowed was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `used for the purpose of the business despite adverse comments by the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Assessing Officer. It was further held that the assessee has not submitted '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `any details in respect of loans availed '>
   <String `of '>
   <String `and loans issued and thus failed to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `establish the genuineness of the transaction. In absence of any new cred'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ible evidence placed before him, he held that the onus of proving that the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `borrowed money has not been utilised for no business purposes was on the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessee which has not been discharged. On the issue of commercial expe'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `diency, it was stated that '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has failed to show any commercial '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 117>
   <String `expediency and therefore the view of the learned Assessing Officer is '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `correct. Accordingly, he confirmed the disallowance.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
