   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `64.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <String ` '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `The learned authorised representative specifically referred to the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessment order where the disallowances made. He referred to page No. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `277 of the paper book which is a summary of inter corporate deposits for '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the '>
   <String `financial year 2016-17. He further stated that there are two parties'>
   <String `,'>
   <String ` '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `namely'>
   <String `,'>
   <String ` Essar '>
   <String `S'>
   <String `teel India Ltd. and Essar Ltd. to whom the inter corporate '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `deposit is given but no interest is charged. It was stated that looking to the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `position of the debtor'>
   <String `-'>
   <String `assessee was not able to charge any interest thereon. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `He referred to page No'>
   <String `s'>
   <String `. 191-192 of the paper book wherein as per '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `paragraph No. (B) the interest on loans and advances to group companies '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `was explained. It was stated that company has given an inter corporate '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `deposit to group concern during the business. The source of this inter '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `corporate deposits was mixed, i. e., out of internal accruals and out of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `inter corporate deposits received. As may be seen from the financial state'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ment, it has in all cases charged interest on inter corporate deposits '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `granted. However, the interest has also been charged at rates higher than '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the rates at which the source of funds has been borrowed. During the year, '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the assessee would not charge any interest on loan given to Essar Steel '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `India Ltd. and Essar Dredging Ltd., because of their financial and opera'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `tional challenges and the strong likelihood of not receiving those interest. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `The management of the company in larger interest of recovery of inter '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `corporate deposits decided not to charge the interest for this year as is '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `evident from the financial statement. Then he relied extensively on the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `submission made by the assessee at page No. 1934 of paper book. The '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned authorised representative further referred to the paper book page '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `No. 307 (page Nos. 314-315).'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
