   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `69.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` We have carefully considered the rival contention and perused the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `orders of the lower authorities. The issue is of about the disallowance of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the interest expenditure on ICD of Rs. 1,58'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `12'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `00,000. The fact shows that '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has incurred interest expenditure to the tune of Rs. 1'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `009.57 '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `crores and has received interest of Rs. 142 crores as interest income. On '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ICD with related parties interest expenditure of Rs. 395.04 crores were '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `paid, and interest received was of Rs. 253.50 crores from Essar '>
   <String `O'>
   <String `il and '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Rs.'>
   <Char EnSpace>
   <String `141.54 crores of security deposit against which '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `received interest of only Rs. 95.38 crores. It is also a fact admitted that '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `though in the corporate deposits have been advanced in the course of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `business however no interest has been charged on certain deposits during '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the year the reason being advanced by the assessee is of “commercial expe'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `diency”. During the course of appellate proceedings, the learned Commis'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `sioner of Income-tax (Appeals) has categorically noted that whether the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `funds borrowed was used for the business purposes, no details were '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `furnished by the assessee. Page No. 277 of the paper book filed by the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessee clearly shows that as on the end of March 31, 2016 total '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `outstanding inter corporate deposits were Rs. 2,57,177 lakhs. The deposits '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `with Essar '>
   <String `S'>
   <String `teel Ltd. at the beginning of the year was Rs. 30,552.62 lakhs '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `and from Essar '>
   <String `D'>
   <String `redging Ltd. of Rs. 1'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `23,502.78 lakhs.'>
   <String ` '>
   <String `On both these '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `accounts, '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has not charged any interest. These ICD is assigned '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `on the last day of the financial year and therefore are not outstanding at '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the end of the year. The only reason advanced by the assessee is that the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `financial condition of the debtor was not good and therefore '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `did not charge any interest on these deposits. Except submissions made '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `before the lower authorities, no evidence of commercial expediency was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `submitted before us. However, the decision of the co-ordinate Bench in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
