    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `Nayara Energy Ltd. '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `v.'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `Italics'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` Asst. CIT'>
   <ElementEnd `Title'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `CRTo'>
   <ElementEnd `Reference'>
   <String `, M. A. No. 332/Mum/'>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `2022 in I. T. A. No. 777/Mum/2022 for assessment year 2016-17 decided on '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `February 6, 2023 '>
   <String `was discussed. The miscellaneous application was only '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `with respect to the restoration of the appeal to the Assessing Officer on '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `that issue in I. T. A. No. which was then decided by the co-ordinate Bench '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `and deleted the interest disallowance. However, the learned authorised '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `representative himself submitted that the whole issue is on different '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `context. It is not the case that '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has huge non-interest'>
   <String ` '>
   <String `bearing '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `surplus/own funds then the amount advanced to the sister concern on '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `which no interest is charged. As on March 31, 2017 the total equity of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessee is only Rs. 67.08 crores. We have also carefully looked that the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `page No. 192 of the paper book wherein a letter dated December 17, 2019 '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `is placed before the learned Assessing Officer. On careful perusal of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `above letter, it was simply statement of judicial principles without any '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `substantive factual details filed before the Assessing Officer or the lower '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `authorities. It is also to be seen that the during this year the interest '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `charged by the assessee is Rs'>
   <String `.'>
   <String ` 9'>
   <String `.'>
   <String `472.53 crores whereas the interest repaid is '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `also a negative figure (page No. 277 of the paper book). It is also to be seen '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `that the outstanding inter corporate deposit of Essar '>
   <String `S'>
   <String `teel India Ltd. was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Rs'>
   <String `.'>
   <String ` 22,478 lakhs on which outstanding interest was Rs'>
   <String `.'>
   <String ` 80.74 lakhs and in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the case of another company the outstanding inter corporate deposit was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Rs. 1,19,335 '>
   <String `l'>
   <String `a'>
   <String `kh'>
   <String `s and the outstanding interest was of Rs. 4'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `207 lakhs. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Thus, '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has not used borrowed funds for the purposes of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `business but has advanced the same to the sister concern without charging '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `any interest. In view of this we do not find any infirmity in the order of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned lower authorities in disallowing interest expenditure of Rs. 158.12 '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `crores under section 36(1)(iii) of the Act. In the result ground No'>
   <String `s'>
   <String `. '>
   <String `3-'>
   <String `5 of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the appeal are dismissed.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
