 <Para 
  <Unique 78684553>
  <PgfTag `s10'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77344558>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Bold'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77365611>
    <ETag `Bold'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `71.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` The brief fact'>
   <String `s'>
   <String ` of the case shows that during the year the assessee '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `has made investment of Rs. 3'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `033.21 crores in the above company. Note '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `No. 56 to the annual account also refers of the above investment. The '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `assessee was asked to produce various details with respect to the above '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `company. The assessee submitted that investment of Rs. 3'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `033.21 crores '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 124>
   <String `were made in three trenches on June 29, 2019, September 29, 2016 and '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `December 29, 2016. The allotment of the shares took place on September '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `30, 2016 and February 23, 2017. This subsidiary company was incorporated '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `into 2015 and did not have any business activities before such investment '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `was made. It was the claim of the assessee that the above investment was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `meant to carry out trading activity, however, no such activities could be '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `carried out because of the prevalent market conditions. In August 2017, '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `these shares of the subsidiary company were brought back from the asses'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `see. Therefore, in this entire process of less than one year the assessee '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `incurred a loss of Rs. 127.93 crores on the transaction. The Assessing '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Officer further noted that over and above the above loss, the assessee has '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `also debited finance cost of Rs. 171.57 crores in its books of account as '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `specific finance cost incurred towards investment in a subsidiary. Before '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the Assessing Officer no documents in relation to the above proposed plan '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `of acquisition of the subsidiary company for the purpose of trading was '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `produced and further the record suggested that no business happened in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `that company. Therefore, the learned Assessing Officer reached at a '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `conclusion that '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee has provided that finance, fund movement '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `shows that once the funds landed in its books, there is nothing brought on '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `record to prove that this investment was in relation to the business. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Accordingly, he disallowed the sum of Rs. 171,57,00,000 of the interest '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `expenditure.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
