    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `72.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` When the issue was challenged before the learned Commissioner of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Income-tax (Appeals) '>
   <String `the '>
   <String `assessee submitted an explanation for commer'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `cial expediency along with the relevant judicial precedents for allowability '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `of expenses in the hands of the holding company. '>
   <String `The '>
   <String `a'>
   <String `ssessee submitted '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `that though the intended activity of trading did not fructify however the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `subsidiary had paid amount equivalent to the equity investment to a '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `potential supplier of motor spirit during the year. The amounts transferred '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `were unsecured and carried interest of 5 per cent. per annum up to the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `date of delivery of supply. The products were initially scheduled to be '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `delivered by the supplier to the subsidiary in the month of December 2016. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `The contract delivery date was scheduled for deliveries to take place in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `September 2017 as per contracts entered. Subsequently the transaction did '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `not materialise and hence the subsidiary decided to buy'>
   <String `-'>
   <String `back the shares in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the '>
   <String `financial year 2017-18. Therefore, it was the claim that the amount of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `interest paid by the assessee on the investment made in a subsidiary '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `company should be allowed as a deduction as there was a business rational '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `for making investment into the subsidiary company. It was also submitted '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `that the sanction letter from ICICI Bank and '>
   <String `A'>
   <String `xis Bank clearly shows that '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 126>
   <String `the facilities were granted for making overseas investment after the due '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `diligence by those bankers and end'>
   <String `-'>
   <String `user certificates were obtained from '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the auditors. The learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals) categor'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ically noted that subsidiary was not carrying out any business, no docu'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ments in relation to the proposed plan has been furnished before the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Assessing Officer, no business actually happened in that company and in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the process the company incurred a loss of Rs. 171.57 crores on account of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `interest and Rs. 127.93 crores on loss on sale of shares. Except citing the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `judicial precedents, no substantive information on facts were produced '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `before the Assessing Officer. The assessee failed to provide the financial '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `statements of the subsidiary, fund movement in the books of the subsid'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `iary'>
   <String `,'>
   <String ` etc. In view of absence of any details from the side of the assessee, the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals) held that there is nothing '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `brought on record to clearly prove that this investment was in relation to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the business of the assessee. Accordingly, he confirmed the disallowance.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
