   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `74.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <String ` '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `The learned Departmental representative submitted that no details '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `were submitted by the assessee before the learned Assessing Officer. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Therefore, the addition has rightly been confirmed by disallowing the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `interest expenditure. He further submitted that if the additional evidence '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `were admitted, the learned Assessing Officer must get an opportunity to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `verify the same. He otherwise supported the orders of the learned lower '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `authorities.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 78684614>
  <PgfTag `s10'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77344736>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Bold'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77365842>
    <ETag `Bold'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `75.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` We have carefully considered the rival contention and perused the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `orders of the learned lower authorities. The brief fact'>
   <String `s'>
   <String ` of the case shows '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `that assessee has made investment in a subsidiary company of Rs. 3'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `033.21 '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `crores in Ennegaon Ltd.'>
   <String `,'>
   <String ` Mauritius consisting of 450 lakhs equity shares of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `1 US dollar each. This fact is evident at note No. 16 (investments) in the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `annual accounts wherein two footnotes are also given. One of the foot'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `notes also referred to another note at note No. 56 which has already been '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `referred to by us in the earlier grounds. As no other details were submitted '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `by the assessee except relying on certain judicial precedents and raising '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `plea of commercial expediency, the disallowance was confirmed by the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `lower authorities.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 78684621>
  <PgfTag `s10'>
  <ParaLine 
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77344771>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Bold'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 77365853>
    <ETag `Bold'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `76.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` Now before us the assessee has submitted annual accounts of the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `subsidiary company as well as the borrowings made from bankers for '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `making such investment. These are the additional evidence along with the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `note of the board of directors filed by the assessee before us which we have '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `admitted. Therefore, if the additional evidence is admitted, it needs to be '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `examined by the learned Assessing Officer first. In view of this we restore '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `this ground of appeal back to the file of the learned Assessing Officer with '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `a direction to the assessee to substantiate before the learned Assessing '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Officer that the interest expenditure incurred by the assessee on invest'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ment made in a subsidiary company is allowable as deduction. Merely '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `relying on the judicial precedent bereft of the facts of the case and unsub'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `stantiated shelter business expediency without factually providing business '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `expediency, will not help the case of the assessee. The learned Assessing '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Officer also needs to examine note No. 7 of accounts of subsidiary '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `company and whether the assessee has any interest in that transaction or '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `not. The learned Assessing Officer may also examine the sanction letters of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the banks on this issues, mere board notes will not suffice the facts of busi'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ness expediency. The learned Assessing Officer may examine the details '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `submitted by the assessee and after enquiry on facts, decide the issue '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `afresh about the allowability of interest expenditure of Rs. 1'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `71'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `57'>
   <String `,'>
   <String `00,000. It '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 130>
   <String `would be the duty of the assessee and the onus to explain before the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned Assessing Officer that such interest expenditure is deductible. The '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `learned Assessing Officer may also grant an opportunity of hearing, if '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FDW  -1.0%>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `requested, before deciding the issue afresh. In view of this ground Nos. 6-7'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `of the appeal is allowed with above direction.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
