   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `7.'>
   <ElementEnd `Bold'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` It was submitted that the notice so issued under section 148 was in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `clear contravention of the mandatory requirement of faceless proceedings '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `stipulated under the Income-tax Act post issuance of notification by the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Ministry of Finance, Government of India dated March 29, 2022 under sec'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `tion 144B of the Act. It was submitted that after issuance of the said noti'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `fication on March 29, 2022, the notice under section 148 ought to have '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `been issued by the Faceless Assessment Unit and not by the '>
   <String `j'>
   <String `urisdictional '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Assessing Officer. It was accordingly submitted that the notice so issued '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `under section 148 has clearly been issued without jurisdiction. In this '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `regard, our reference was drawn to the decision of '>
   <String `c'>
   <String `o-ordinate Bench in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the '>
   <String `case of '>
